        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: use Object.hasOwn instead of in operator in usage bar translator",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where `key in table` matches inherited `Object.prototype` properties (`toString`, `valueOf`, `constructor`) instead of only own properties.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nReplace `key in table` with `Object.hasOwn(table, key)` in alias lookup and case table lookup.\n\n## User Impact\n\nFixes incorrect usage bar rendering when keys coincide with prototype property names.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```\nsrc/auto-reply/usage-bar/translator.test.ts\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n     Tests  15 passed (15)\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 9.65s\n```\n\nIncludes 2 new regression tests:\n- `toString` with explicit alias entry resolves correctly (not Object.prototype)\n- `constructor` without alias passes through instead of hitting Object.prototype\n- Map case `toString`/`constructor` fall back to `_default` correctly",
